</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8B0743163DFFD2B59EE1086FDDCFF0" blockId="43.[160,1156,523,652]" pageId="43" pageNumber="359">
<taxonomicName id="4C347CC0163DFFD2B59EE1086A26CF3B" authorityName="Forel" authorityYear="1907" box="[160,383,559,583]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="359" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pauper">
<emphasis id="B940DB51163DFFD2B59EE1086A26CF3B" box="[160,383,559,583]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="359">Tetramorium pauper</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found nesting inside a small decayed twig. The soil was moist due to irrigation of the date palm orchard. Several workers were nesting under a rock. A nest series was collected from a dry leaf litter next to a date palm tree using a sifting tray.
</paragraph>
